	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64589289"><p>Yes, it does, because at some stage it makes sense to get a cached and simplified picture of the basic facts of the world to get you bootstrapped, and it beats re-discovering the bicycle from scratch. But the sooner you are pushed out of the comfort zone of rote, the better you become at dealing with change and challenges and doing something new and important. And the more work you put into it, the better you get.</p><p>Or at least this is my experience.</p></div>
